Plant collected .8 km NE of Saimadodyi. It is found abundantly in the mountains of Sierra Perijá at higher altitudes than Saimadodyi, from 700 m to 1000 m of altitude. The soil is normally sandy dark brown, quite humid and rich in humus. Tropical environment with an annual average of 2 C (at 150 m. of altitude) and 3500 mm or rain with high humidity and a dry season from December 15 til March 15 (with rain at least once a week)
